New Funds Aim 5 Billion Dollars at Markets, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   K e i t h   J e n k i n s
-- 
2011-06-12T09:38:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/new-funds-aim-5-billion-dollars-at-markets-telegraph-reports.html
Blackstone Group LP (BX)  and Avenue
Capital are raising funds to invest $5 billion in financial
markets, the Sunday Telegraph said.  Private equity house Blackstone and debt specialist Avenue
Capital are talking to potential customers, primarily in the
U.S., the London-based newspaper reported, without saying where
it got the information.  Blackstone is establishing a $3 billion GSO Capital
Opportunities Fund II through GSO Capital Partners to invest in
private equity and other private transactions, the Telegraph
reported. Avenue Capital, founded by  Marc Lasry , is raising as
much as $2 billion to invest in U.S. companiesâ€™ debt, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
